## Commands

- Dev: `dev.bat` or `npm run tauri dev`
- Build: `build.bat` or `npm run tauri build -- --no-bundle` ‚Üí **`src-tauri/target/release/koi-monitor.exe` only** (no MSI/NSIS; `bundle.active: false`)
- Setup: `setup.bat` (admin, first install)
- Frontend only: `npm run build`

## Principles

- Minimum code that solves the problem. No speculative features or abstractions.
- Surgical changes only ‚Äî match existing style, don't refactor unrelated code.
- Define success criteria before coding; verify with `npm run build` + `cargo check`.
- All Tauri IPC goes through `src/services/api.ts`, not scattered `invoke()` calls.
- Prefer granular Zustand selectors over full-store subscriptions.

## Telemetry flow

1. Rust background thread (1 s) updates shared state ‚Üí `app.emit("telemetry-update", SystemInfo)`
2. Rust gaming thread (2 s) ‚Üí `GamingLatencyTracker::sample()` ‚Üí `app.emit("gaming-latency-update", snapshot)`
3. `useTelemetryPoller` listens to both events; DNS still polled on `settings.dnsInterval`
4. `get_system_info` / `get_gaming_latency` kept as IPC fallbacks

